'''{{mp|(163364) 2002 OD|20}}''' is an [[asteroid]], classified as a [[near-Earth object]] and [[potentially hazardous asteroid]] of the [[Apollo asteroid|Apollo group]], likely smaller than one kilometer in diameter.<ref name=jpl-close/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://brinktest.lpl.arizona.edu/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/TargetAsteroidsList_v7_1406122.pdf |title=Target Asteroids! List of Near-Earth Asteroids}}</ref>
It was scheduled to be observed by [[Goldstone Deep Space Communications Complex|Goldstone]] [[radar astronomy|radar]] in May 2013.<ref name=Goldstone/> It has a well determined orbit and will make a close approach to [[Earth]] on 23 May 2013, at a distance of {{convert|0.0387|AU|km mi|abbr=on|lk=on}}.<ref name=jpl-close/><ref name=Goldstone>{{cite web | url=http://echo.jpl.nasa.gov/asteroids/goldstone_asteroid_schedule.html | title=Goldstone Asteroid Schedule | accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> It is due to make another close pass on 23 May 2131, coming as close as 0.0248 [[Astronomical Unit|AU]].<ref name=jpl-close/> It was discovered on 21 July 2002 by astronomers of the [[Near-Earth Asteroid Tracking]] survey at [[Palomar Observatory]] in California.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.minorplanetcenter.org/iau/lists/Dangerous.html | title=List Of The Potentially Hazardous Asteroids (PHAs) | publisher=[[Minor Planet Center]] | accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> With an [[Absolute magnitude#Solar System bodies (H)|absolute magnitude]] of 18.8,<ref name=jpl-close/> the diameter is estimated to between 460 and 1030 meters.<ref name="h"/>
